org.hibernate.sql.ast.produce.metamodel.spi

Interface PolymorphicEntityValuedExpressableType<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DomainType<T>, DomainTypeDescriptor<T>, EntityValuedExpressableType<T>, ExpressableType<T>, Navigable<T>, NavigableContainer<T>, Type<T>, Writeable

    public interface PolymorphicEntityValuedExpressableType<T>
extends EntityValuedExpressableType<T>
    A specialized EntityValuedExpressableType for cases where the entity reference named an "unmapped polymorphic" class. E.g. given a query like select o from java.lang.Object o we would ask the consumer for an EntityValuedExpressableType for java.lang.Object and the consumer would return us PolymorphicEntityValuedExpressableType<java.lang.Object> which would contain all mapped entities as its getImplementors().

    Such "unmapped polymorphic" references are only valid in the root from-clause and only one such reference is allow for the query.

    See Also:
